Demo usage of AMT

Gari

13-01-2020

Task: The software should be able to measure the physical traits of a fish. The expected dimensions are shown in the following figure

The software is only able to measure on black background images. The more similar you image to the examples the better the measurement.

In [1]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [3]:
%run ./AMT.py 'S globiceps 20.3 TL.jpg' yes True
In [4]:
%run ./AMT.py 'S quoyi 12.3 SL-15.2 TL.jpg' yes True
In [5]:
# In this example the tail was wrongly detected
%run ./AMT.py 'N tonganus 39.5 SL.jpg' yes True
In [6]:
%run /home/gari/Desktop/folders/Jacobs_resourses/AMT/AMT.py 'C unimaculata 4.4 TL.jpg' yes True
In [17]:
# In this example, the fin and the eye was not detected
%run ./AMT.py 'H harid 40.6 TL.jpg' yes True
In [15]:
# In this example, we change the second input parameter to False, which changes the optimization
# to get the eye, see next picture
%run ./AMT.py 'S schlegeli 15.7 SL-18.8 TL.jpg' yes False
In [19]:
# In this example, we change the input parameter, compere with prior picture
%run ./AMT.py 'S schlegeli 15.7 SL-18.8 TL.jpg' no True
